function.arguments:
{"command": "# Get all agents via getPage(0, 50)
# getPage(uint256,uint256) selector = need to compute
# Let me use the getAll function or try different approach

# First, let's see if I can get the agentList length and individual entries
# agentList(uint256) = 0x4f64b2be

# Get first few agents
for i in 0 1 2 3 4 5; do
  PAD=$(printf '%064x' $i)
  RESULT=$(curl -s -X POST https://mainnet.base.org -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d "{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_call\",\"params\":[{\"to\":\"0x3081aE79B403587959748591bBe1a2c12AeF5167\",\"data\":\"0x4f64b2be${PAD}\"},\"latest\"],\"id\":1}")
  ADDR=$(echo "$RESULT" | node -e "let d='';process.stdin.on('data',c=>d+=c);process.stdin.on('end',()=>console.log(JSON.parse(d).result||''))")
  if [ -n "$ADDR" ] && [ "$ADDR" != "0x" ]; then
    echo "$i: $ADDR"
  fi
done"}
